	"Mail_AppleBlood_body": "Hey @,^Have you ever heard of the phrase 'blood from a stone'? What about 'blood from an apple?' Well, I don't think that's actually a real saying, haha, but I just watched the finale of a wonderful show called The Owl House about witches and magic where apples are full of actual blood! I thought I'd come up with a recipe for a juice box version so I'm sending you a copy!^   -Leah",
	"Mail_AppleBlood_title": "Apple Blood Recipe",
	"Mail_ArchonBurger_body": "Hey @!^Have you heard of the critically acclaimed MMORPG Final Fantasy... actually, I don't know if you play online games, but if you ever want to know more, definitely let me know and I can tell you about my favorite game sometime. If you decide you want to play the free trial, you can join my server. Either way, here's a fan recipe on how to put together a delicious meal from the game! I hope you enjoy it!^   -Sebastian",
	"Mail_ArchonBurger_title": "Archon Burger Recipe",
	"Mail_Estus_body": "What's up, @?^I've been playing this really hard game lately called Dark Souls. It's like, incredibly challenging but super fun. The adrenaline rush when you finally take down a massive boss that you've been smashing your face against for hours is the greatest reward. Let me know when you've got a break from working the farm and I can let you borrow my copy of the first game. Or if you've got too much choring to do, you can use this recipe as a pick me up!",
	"Mail_Estus_title": "Estus Recipe",
	"Mail_GrayStuff_body": "Hey @!^Did you ever grow up dreaming about being royalty? I know my favorite thing to do as a kid was pretend I was a princess in a fairy tale. My favorite is definitely Beauty and the Beast. Have you ever seen the movie version? The enchanted rose is soooo pretty! Apparently there's a made-up recipe for the 'Gray Stuff'. ...Though I guess it was probably something else in the movie... Here's the recipe from a blog I follow. It's super sweet!^   -Haley",
	"Mail_GrayStuff_title": "Gray Stuff Recipe",
	"Mail_GreenEggsandHam_body": "Hey @!^Did you know there's such things as green eggs? I was told they come from dinosaurs! Anyway, I got one and fried it up with a big tofu steak and it reminded me of that children's book from when I was a kid. You know the one with the guy chasing around his friend? Don't tell Sam I made this, though, he'll never let me hear the end of it... Anyway, here's the recipe if you need a double dose of protein!^   -Alex",
	"Mail_GreenEggsandHam_title": "Green Eggs and Ham Recipe",
	"Mail_KikisCake_body": "Hi @,^The other day I decided to bake a rendition of a cake from one of my *favorite* animated movies: Kiki's Delivery Service! It's about a witch who moves away from home to set out on her own adventure in a far away town on the ocean. She reminds me a little of you in that way, so I thought I'd share the recipe with you!^   -Abigail",
	"Mail_KikisCake_title": "Kiki's Cake Recipe",
	"Mail_KrabbyPatty_body": "Hello @,^I wanted to share a recipe with you from a show the kids love to watch. I'll admit, when we take a break from studies, it's one of my favorites to watch with them because the characters are so interesting. I especially like Sandy and Squidward. If you have any questions about the recipe, let me know and I can elaborate.^   -Penny^^(P.S. The secret ingredient is love!)",
	"Mail_KrabbyPatty_title": "Krabby Patty Recipe",
	"Mail_LembasBread_body": "Dear @,^The other day I was reminded of one my favorite stories, The Lord of the Rings. It involves a fellowship of nine adventurers on a journey to thwart a great evil and destroy a mysterious gold ring. The passage I love the most involves the heroes pitted against a terrible foe made of fire and ash! The delimma, proving too daunting, causes the valiant heroes to have to flee... The tragic fall of the wise and gentle wizard always moves me to tears. I can lend you the book if you would like to read it, but for now, please take this recipe inspired from the setting. May it be you find your strength!^   -Elliott",
	"Mail_LembasBread_title": "Lembas Bread Recipe",
	"Mail_Potion_body": "Greeings, @.^In my studies of distant realms of crystal blue, I encountered whispers of a tonic once favored by warriors of great renown. A bottled draught said to sharpen the mind and steel the spirit before battle. While its origins lie beyond even my scrying, I have recreated something... similar. Use this knowledge wisely and perhaps you will glimpse the same boundless vitality those distant warriors of light once possessed.^   -M. Rasmodius, Wizard",
	"Mail_Potion_title": "Potion Recipe",
	"Mail_RedKibble_body": "Hello @!^I wanted to say I've gotten really into a new science fiction series lately, so I used that tofu to test out a type of ration they eat in the book. It's made from things the society learned to grow in space with very limited resources, which I find truly fascinating! If you ever want to read it, I'd be happy to lend it to you... It's called The Expanse! I hope this recipe I came up with convinces you it would be worth the time!^   -Maru",
	"Mail_RedKibble_title": "Red Kibble Recipe",
	"Mail_SakumaDrops_body": "Hi @,^I recently watched a very powerful and emotional movie about two siblings going through an unbelievable harship. While I took so much away from it, I was feeling like I needed to lift my spirits and tried my hand at recreating the jewel-like candies featured in the film. I'm sending along the recipe in hopes that these bring you a lot of good energy.",
	"Mail_SakumaDrops_title": "Sakuma Drops Recipe",
	"Mail_SpinachPuffs_body": "Hey @!,^I'm not normally a veggie kind of guy, but one of my favorite movies ever is The Emperor's New Groove. I watched it so often I'm pretty sure I can recite the lines by memory. If you know the movie, you know the best character in it makes these spinach puffs. They're actually pretty good if you don't burn them. Here's the recipe!^   -Shane",
	"Mail_SpinachPuffs_title": "Spinach Puffs Recipe",
	"Mail_WonkaBar_body": "Hi @,^Did I ever tell you one of my favorite books growing up was Charlie and the Chocolate Factory? I'm not the biggest fan of sweets, but I like to keep them on hand for when someone comes into the clinic and needs a little boost when they're feeling down. All in moderation, of course! If you ever feel like making the iconic candy bar from the book, I've sent you a recipe to try out. I hope you like it!^   -Harvey",
	"Mail_WonkaBar_title": "Wonka Bar Recipe",
	
	"Leah_dialogue.AppleBlood": "Wow thanks! It's a bit more gelatinous than I expected, haha!",
	"Sebastian_dialogue.ArchonBurger": "Incredible! Let me know if you ever want to play the game!",
	"Sam_dialogue.Estus": "Thanks! Praise the sun!",
	"Haley_dialogue.GrayStuff": "Thanks. It *is* delicious!",
	"Alex_dialogue.GreenEggsandHam": "I do so like green eggs and ham!",
	"Abigail_dialogue.KikisCake": "Thank you! Let's watch the movie together some time!",
	"Penny_dialogue.KrabbyPatty": "'Who lives in a pineapple under the sea?'",
	"Elliott_dialogue.LembasBread": "Oh thank you! Perhaps just a nibble...",
	"Wizard_dialogue.Potion": "Thank you. The flavor is an acquired taste.",
	"Maru_dialogue.RedKibble": "Thank you! Or as they say in the books: 'Taki beratna / sésata!'",
	"Emily_dialogue.SakumaDrops": "Hey, thanks! Each one is a cherished moment!",
	"Shane_dialogue.SpinachPuffs": "Oooh, thanks! They're best when they're still hot!",
	"Harvey_dialogue.WonkaBar": "Thank you very much! I'll keep this at the clinic for a rainy day.",
	
	
